gov.usgs.anss.cd11

Class ChannelSubframe

  • java.lang.Object
    • gov.usgs.anss.cd11.ChannelSubframe

  • public class ChannelSubframe
extends java.lang.Object
    This class represents a CD1.1 channel subframe and has methods for reading that information from a positioned byte buffer. The subframe is detailed in the manual as table 2.10. This class was implemented based on the Version 0.3 version of the manual dated 18 Dec 2002

      • getSamples

        public int getSamples(int[] samples)
               throws CanadaException
        get the data samples from this subframe, this routine does all of the decoding of various allowed formats for the data.
        Parameters:
        samples - A user buffer to conain the samples. It must be big enough!
        Returns:
        The number of samples decoded
        Throws:
        CanadaException - If detected during decompression of Canadian Compressed frame
